Hello, Mon.

192
00:14:58,470 --> 00:14:59,310
Where are you, Kim?

193
00:14:59,990 --> 00:15:01,700
I saved you a seat in the stargazing dome.

194
00:15:02,440 --> 00:15:04,460
There are some spots left for this round.

195
00:15:05,210 --> 00:15:06,140
Would you like to join me?

196
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:08,380
If you would, you need to hurry.

197
00:15:08,400 --> 00:15:09,710
The show starts in ten minutes.

198
00:15:11,140 --> 00:15:11,910
Okay, okay.

199
00:15:11,930 --> 00:15:13,620
I’ll be right there.

200
00:15:24,360 --> 00:15:26,380
Mon asked me to watch a show
at the dome with him.

201
00:15:27,440 --> 00:15:27,960
See?

202
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,030
Mon seems okay with you.

203
00:15:31,510 --> 00:15:32,510
What are you so afraid of?

204
00:15:42,080 --> 00:15:43,010
Because I don’t know.

205
00:15:47,750 --> 00:15:50,450
I don’t know if he has feelings for me

206
00:15:52,580 --> 00:15:53,810
or if he’s just being nice.

207
00:15:59,770 --> 00:16:00,580
I don’t know...

208
00:16:02,890 --> 00:16:05,400
if he’s always just thought of me as a friend.

209
00:16:11,070 --> 00:16:13,100
What if I confess

210
00:16:16,430 --> 00:16:18,150
and he doesn’t feel the same way?

211
00:16:23,060 --> 00:16:24,150
At least you tried.

212
00:16:25,160 --> 00:16:26,180
He will like you, for sure.

213
00:16:31,510 --> 00:16:32,220
It’s okay, man.

214
00:17:06,849 --> 00:17:07,800
Do you need some help?

215
00:17:08,710 --> 00:17:09,329
No.

216
00:17:10,220 --> 00:17:11,020
I want to do it myself.

217
00:17:11,579 --> 00:17:12,630
Been working on it all night anyway.

218
00:17:18,420 --> 00:17:19,339
You won’t be able to.

219
00:17:19,460 --> 00:17:20,290
Let me help.

220
00:17:20,609 --> 00:17:22,000
I said I want to do it myself.

221
00:17:22,190 --> 00:17:22,810
Stay out of it.

222
00:17:27,589 --> 00:17:28,520
Let me see.

223
00:17:31,450 --> 00:17:32,830
It’s asking which choice is wrong.

224
00:17:33,430 --> 00:17:35,800
That means you need to
find these three values first.

225
00:17:36,490 --> 00:17:38,220
First, how do you find the average?

226
00:17:38,600 --> 00:17:40,020
You add up all the numbers
and divide by how many there are.

227
00:17:40,560 --> 00:17:41,210
Very good.

228
00:17:41,670 --> 00:17:43,210
But you need to rearrange the numbers first.

229
00:17:43,360 --> 00:17:44,760
The given problem doesn’t
arrange them for you.

230
00:17:45,100 --> 00:17:46,160
Do this until it becomes a habit.

231
00:17:46,570 --> 00:17:48,910
After rearranging, add everything up

232
00:17:49,080 --> 00:17:51,020
and divide by the number, which is five.

233
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:53,350
So, what’s the total added value?

234
00:17:54,460 --> 00:17:55,220
31.

235
00:17:55,650 --> 00:17:57,670
31 divided by 5 equals 6.2.

236
00:17:58,090 --> 00:17:59,160
That’s the average.

237
00:17:59,230 --> 00:18:00,460
Now, the median.

238
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:01,880
What is it?

239
00:18:02,670 --> 00:18:03,700
The middle number.

240
00:18:04,140 --> 00:18:07,060
So, what's the middle number
after rearranging the set?

241
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:08,760
4.

242
00:18:09,510 --> 00:18:10,450
What’s the mode?

243
00:18:11,030 --> 00:18:12,350
The number that occurs most often.

244
00:18:14,030 --> 00:18:14,710
Which is 4.

245
00:18:15,190 --> 00:18:15,700
Yes.

246
00:18:16,430 --> 00:18:17,200
That’s it.

247
00:18:21,110 --> 00:18:23,110
Why wasn’t it this easy when I did it myself?

248
00:18:23,530 --> 00:18:24,580
Because you’re impatient.

249
00:18:25,780 --> 00:18:28,510
You said you’ve been working on this all night.

250
00:18:28,750 --> 00:18:29,850
That’s dangerous, you know?

251
00:18:30,700 --> 00:18:32,160
There’s a time limit during exams.

252
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:36,690
Keep in mind that you should skip the problems
you can’t solve and move on to the next ones.

253
00:18:37,180 --> 00:18:39,530
If you stubbornly focus on the same problem,

254
00:18:40,310 --> 00:18:43,100
you’ll get stuck and won’t make any progress.

255
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:51,870
So, when is our next tutoring session?

256
00:18:52,860 --> 00:18:53,740
